3 O. For purposes of subsection F of this section, “great bodily
4 injury” means bone fracture,; protracted and obvious disfigurement,;
5 protracted loss or impairment of the function of a body part, organ,
6 or mental faculty,; prolonged pain or significant discomfort;
7 concussion; injuries to more than ten percent (10%) of the body
8 including, but not limited to, bruises, swelling, scratches, and
9 scrapes, in the presence of a minor; or substantial risk of death.
10 P. Any pleas of guilty or nolo contendere or finding of guilt
11 to a violation of any provision of this section shall constitute a
